:: Tavern [act1]
The Rusted Anchor smells of tar, wet wool and yesterday's chowder. Conversations die when you enter, then resume at half volume. Saltmere does not love strangers.

[[Ask about the lighthouse|Rumors]]
[[Order a drink and listen|Drink]]
[[Ask the barkeep about Mira|Barkeep]]

:: Rumors [act1]
"The Light doesn't burn oil," mutters a fisherman into his cup. "Never has. Old keeper families knew what it really burns. Why d'you think Mira never took an apprentice?"

<<set $knowsRumor to true>>

[[Head for the lighthouse|Lighthouse Gate]]
[[Back to the bar|Tavern]]

:: Drink [act1]
The chowder is better than it smells. Around you, Saltmere talks: the herring are gone, the Council raised the mooring fees again, and nobody — nobody — walks the cliff path after dark anymore.

[[Back to the bar|Tavern]]

:: Secret Cellar [act1 secret]
Behind the barrels, a trapdoor. The cellar below is older than the tavern above it — older, maybe, than Saltmere. On the far wall someone has carved the same spiral that is stamped on the lighthouse door.

[[Climb back up|Tavern]]
